## Rules

1. `corroborated` ONLY if the page text DIRECTLY states the claim.
   "Page is consistent with the claim being true" is NOT enough.
2. `contradicted` ONLY if the page text DIRECTLY refutes it (e.g. claim
   says HQ is Berlin and the page says Munich).
3. `unconfirmed` otherwise — including silent pages.
4. `confidence` ∈ [0, 1]. Use ≥0.9 only when the page verbatim contains
   the predicate/object pair.
5. `evidence_snippet`: smallest contiguous text from the page that
   supports your verdict. ≤1500 chars. Verbatim, no paraphrase.
6. `contradiction_detail`: only when status="contradicted". Render both
   sides verbatim: "Rep said X; <url> says Y."
7. `reasoning`: 2–4 sentences. Be specific.

## Output

Strict JSON conforming to the Output schema. No prose, no markdown fences.

{
  "status": "corroborated|unconfirmed|contradicted",
  "confidence": 0.0,
  "evidence_url": "{{ evidence_url }}",
  "evidence_snippet": "<text or null>",
  "contradiction_detail": "<text or null>",
  "reasoning": "<2-4 sentences>"
}
